\lim\limits_{h\to 0}\frac{\cos(2x+2h)-\cos(2x)}{h}=\lim\limits_{h\to 0}\frac{(2x+2h)-2x}{(2x+2h)-2x}\frac{\cos(2x+2h)-\cos(2x)}{h}=\\\lim\limits_{h\to 0}\frac{\cos(2x+2h)-\cos(2x)}{(2x+2h)-2x}\frac{(2x+2h)-2x}{h}
=\lim\limits_{h\to 0}\frac{\cos(u+g)-\cos(u)}{g}\cdot2 = \lim\limits_{g\to 0}\frac{\cos(u+g)-\cos(u)}{g}\cdot2 = \\2\lim\limits_{g\to 0}\frac{\cos u\cos g - \sin u \sin g -\cos u}{g} = 2\left (\lim\limits_{g\to 0}\frac{\cos u(\cos g - 1)}{g} - \sin u \right) = 2\left (\lim\limits_{g\to 0}\cos u\frac{\cos^2 g - 1}{g(\cos g + 1)} - \sin u \right)= 2\left (\lim\limits_{g\to 0}\cos u\frac{\sin g}{\cos g + 1} - \sin u \right)=-2\sin u = -2 \sin(2x)
